snippet.title: Trump hosts top tech CEOs at White House: Bill Gates, Mark Zuckerberg, Sam Altman, Tim Cook & more
snippet.description:
President Trump hosted some of the top technology CEOs at the White House for dinner on Wednesday. 

The guest list included Microsoft cofounder Bill Gates, Apple CEO Tim Cook, Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg and other executives, according to the White House. 

One notable absence: Elon Musk.  

he event follows a session of the new Artificial Intelligence Education Task Force, chaired by First lady Melania Trump, which aims to foster AI awareness and education among K-12 students.

snippet.title: Cardi B‚Äôs Meme-filled Courtroom Drama
snippet.description:
Watch The Full Philip DeFranco Show: https://www.youtube.com/defranco?sub_confirmation=1
Subscribe for more Quickie News: https://www.youtube.com/defranco?sub_confirmation=1

So, Cardi B is currently in court for a civil suit, and it‚Äôs going something like this:
‚ÄúYesterday you had black hair, short hair, today it‚Äôs blonde, which one is your real hair? Or is are they both real?...(laughing) They‚Äôre wigs!‚Äù 
‚ÄúDo you have any affiliation at this time with a gang?‚Äù  
‚ÄúYour fingernails, can you show them to us for all of us to see? How long are those fingernails?
‚ÄúI said bitch, get the fuck out of my face, why are you in my face, why are you recording me? Ain‚Äôt you supposed to be security?..say it again..you want me to say it to her face?... I want you to say to her face what you said on that day.‚Äù 
‚ÄúYou said she‚Äôs bigger than you, is that correct?..absolutely‚Ä¶how do you know that? (cardi points to her eyes then to the crowd then to her eyes and to the crowd while nodding like the lawyer is a moron)...I mean, look.‚Äù 
So those are just some highlight clips from this trial, which are going incredibly viral online as the case plays out. 
As for what it is even about, a security guard has accused Cardi of assaulting her in 2018 at a OBGYN‚Äôs office in Beverly Hills and is seeking $24 million in damages. 
According to the security guard, she was working at a building where Cardi had a medical appointment and was doing rounds when she saw Cardi get off the elevator and said out loud, ‚ÄúWow, it‚Äôs Cardi B.‚Äù
And she says this upset Cardi, she felt she had been called out in public, and it prompted her to curse at the guard, threaten her job, spit on her, take a swing at her, and scratch her cheek with her fingernail.
But according to Cardi, this is not how it went down, with her claiming she was frustrated because she believes the guard was recording her, and while they had a heated exchange and went chest to chest, she maintains it was never physical.
‚ÄúDid you ever threaten to get her fired?...No‚Ä¶And I want to be very clear, did you ever spit on Ms. Ellis?..No‚Ä¶Did you ever call Ms Ellis the N word, apologies?...No.‚Äù
‚ÄúDid you ever touch Ammani Ellis's face or nose with your finger?.. No.‚Äù 
‚ÄúShe couldn‚Äôt get a scratch from me because I didn‚Äôt touch her.‚Äù
And so far, a receptionist at the office who intervened did back some of this up:
‚ÄúAt any point in that confrontation did Cardi B cut Ms. Ellis with Cardi‚Äôs finger nails, while you were there?...objection, calls for speculation, overruled‚Ä¶no.‚Äù ‚ÄúDid you hear Cardi B use the n word, you know what I mean by the n word?...yeah, no.‚Äù 
So this trial is playing out both in the real courts and in the court of public opinion.
That latter of which is more amused than anything, not just by the lawyers asking about Cardi‚Äôs hair and nails, but Cardi‚Äôs overall demeanor throughout this. 
People thinking it seems like an SNL skit and that her next project should just be doing comedy.
But of course, it is a real trial that will have a real outcome, and we will have to wait to see what that is. 
But I would love to know your thoughts on what we have seen so far.

snippet.title: "The House On Elmhurst Road" | Jacarie Robinson's Story | OneCrimeTV
snippet.description:
At 6:15pm on October 10, 2023 police in Milwaukee, Wisconsin were dispatched to a house on North Elmhurst Road.  A man named Romuan Moye lived at the residence with his three homeschooled children. Romuan also had a girlfriend as well but she was recently deceased. From around two weeks prior to the day in question, Romuan's daughters had been living with their mother Yalawn Robinson. This meant the only child in Romaun‚Äôs care at this time was his youngest son Jacarie Robinson. Jacarie was 12 years old.

Romuan also has an older son, then 22 year old Jovaeus Moye. Roughly 4 or 5 days prior to the call that dispatched authorities to the house on Elmhurst Road, Jovaeus described visiting his father outside the property. He told authorities that his dad was acting abnormal and repeatedly taking deep breaths for what appeared to be no reason. Jovaeus claims he expressed concern for his father‚Äôs wellbeing and told him to stay in contact before leaving. Jovaeus never entered the house that day.

In the following days Jovaeus and Romuan exchanged messages about the daughters coming over to the house to visit with their father and little brother Jacarie. Romuan agreed to this but when Jovaeus attempted to drop off his little sisters on October 8th, no one answered the door. Ramuan responded via text message saying he wasn‚Äôt home. This was the second time Jovaeus had been to the house and no one answered the door. 

Jovaeus was deeply concerned about his father. Romuan had told him that he‚Äôd been diagnosed with cancer a few years prior to 2023. In the past month he furthered his claim telling his oldest son that the disease had progressed leaving him with very little time left to live. Upon learning this revelation, naturally Jovaeus wanted to spend more time with his dad. But unfortunately, Romuan became evasive and avoidant.

On October 10th Jovaeus found himself at his father‚Äôs door once again with knocks answered by no one. He called out to his father saying, ‚ÄúIf you‚Äôre in there, please come out.‚Äù But still no one responded. Fearing something badly wrong, Jovaeus let himself into his fathers house. And as he made entry, he was confronted with a terrible odour. What he found in that house left him in shock, crying uncontrollably, and prompted the call that dispatched authorities to the house.
